        "title": "Repair invoke-style plain-text tool calls",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Extend invoke-style plain-text tool-call repair for Opus 4.8-style XML output.\n- Preserve ordinary prose examples that mention `<invoke ...>` snippets.\n- Keep existing non-invoke tool-call repair behavior unchanged.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Opus 4.8-style plain-text XML tool calls that arrive as assistant text are normalized into structured tool-call events, while prose examples containing `<invoke ...>` remain visible text.\n\n- Real environment tested: Real OpenClaw gateway installation using the npm package, with hostnames, endpoints, and local paths redacted.\n\n- Exact steps or command run after fix: Start the OpenClaw gateway from the installed npm package; confirm gateway health; feed an invoke-style XML tool-call payload through the after-fix normalization path; feed a prose example containing the same XML shape through visible-text extraction; run focused unit coverage for visible-text and embedded-agent extraction paths.\n\n- Evidence: Copied after-fix terminal output from the real gateway setup and local validation:\n\n```text\n$ openclaw --version\nopenclaw@2026.6.5\n\n$ curl -s http://127.0.0.1:<gateway-port>/health\n{\"ok\":true,\"status\":\"live\"}\n\n$ node ./verify-invoke-toolcall.mjs\ninput:\ncall\n<invoke name=\"exec\">\n<parameter name=\"command\">date</parameter>\n</invoke>\n\nnormalized events:\ntoolcall_start name=exec\ntoolcall_delta arguments={\"command\":\"date\"}\ndone reason=toolUse\n\nvisible-text regression:\ninput: Example:\\n<invoke name=\"Bash\">\\n<parameter name=\"command\">ls</parameter>\\n</invoke>\noutput: Example:\\n<invoke name=\"Bash\">\\n<parameter name=\"command\">ls</parameter>\\n</invoke>\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts src/shared/text/assistant-visible-text.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-utils.test.ts --reporter=dot --maxWorkers=1\n\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  156 passed (156)\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The invoke-style XML payload was promoted to `toolcall_start`, `toolcall_delta`, and `done` with `reason=toolUse`. The ordinary prose example was preserved verbatim instead of being stripped.\n\n- What was not tested: Private provider credentials, private endpoints, and unredacted hostnames are not included. Broader CI coverage is left to the repository workflows.\n\n## Privacy\nNo personal hostnames, private endpoints, credentials, or local paths are included in this PR.",
